cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.SE

The paper focuses on machine learning workflow development and optimization, which is a core topic in the field of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a Scala DSL for defining unified processes for data preprocessing, model specification, and learning, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The optimization techniques used in the paper, such as Max-Flow and NP-Hard problems, are related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper also discusses the development of effective heuristics, which falls under the scope of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
